investigation of the reasons and circumstances of this 
extraordinary event we understand the great difficultly of this 
work 
the kgb will do all thats possible to establish the truth and 
publicize the results of our work he said 
kryuchkov said the kgb was working with prosecutors and the 
interior and health ministries 
the blast was heard 16 miles away and the soviet military chief 
of staff gen mikhail a moiseyev told the official tass news 
agency monday that it had the power of 10000 tons of tnt or half 
the power of the first atomic bomb that was dropped on hiroshima 
japan 
