difficult because of its numbers in the senate and sejm and its 
mass popular support the independent union will have a huge say in 
policy and appointments 
for instance no legislation will be able to get through the new 
national assembly without solidarity votes the senate has a veto 
over all bills and the party lacks enough votes in the sjm to 
override the veto 
there is also the question of naming a new president and forming 
a new government after the new sejm and senate are seated 
theoretically rakowski could keep his post despite having been 
denied a parliament seat but it might be difficult for him to 
function effectively as prime minister after such a loss of face 
and there likely will be calls for someone more popular with the 
voters to head the government 
similarly the sejm and senate are to meet together to name a 
president a newly created executive office with strong powers 
under polands revamped constitution that was designed to be a 
bulwark to keep poland in the soviet bloc 
