poor condition in kansas where the crop was hit hard by the dry 
weather winter wheat was turning color and beginning to ripen in 
texas the harvest was 8 percent completed about 15 percentage 
points behind normal for this time of the season 
rain slowed oklahomas wheat harvest and reduced the quality 
of the unharvested crop the report said in nebraska russian 
