the soviet union has bought an additional 
400000 metric tons of us corn and sorghum for delivery this year 
under a longterm agreement the agriculture department said tuesday 
the grain 300000 tons of corn and 100000 tons of sorghum is 
scheduled for delivery through aug 31 sales were handled by 
private exporters under terms of the current longterm grain supply 
agreement between the two countries 
moscows grain purchases have been at record levels for weeks 
far surpassing chinas recent buying surge 
officials said the latest sales boosted total us corn and wheat 
sales to the soviets in 198889 to a record 205 million tons 
including more than 159 million tons of corn and 46 million tons 
of wheat 
