the communist government demoralized by 
its crushing election defeat again urged victorious solidarity on 
tuesday to join a governing coalition a proposal the union has 
turned down 
it is time for a broad postelection coalition a kind of pact 
for economic reforms and democracy government spokesman zbyslaw 
rykowski told a news conference a communist party spokesman said 
