<TEXT>
interest rates on shortterm treasury 
securities fell in the latest auction to the lowest level this year 
the treasury department sold 64 billion in threemonth bills 
monday at an average discount rate of 817 percent down from 850 
percent last week 
another 64 billion was sold in sixmonth bills at an average 
discount rate of 799 percent down from 836 percent last week 
the rates were the lowest since threemonth bills sold for 814 
percent on dec 19 and sixmonth bills averaged 787 percent on 
nov 14 
the new discount rates understate the actual return to investors 
846 percent for threemonth bills with a 10000 bill selling 
for 979350 and 844 percent for a sixmonth bill selling for 
959610 
</TEXT>
