<TEXT>
sears roebuck and co may announce this week 
where it plans to move its merchandise group and some employees 
say the companys actions suggest it has picked a site out of 
state a newspaper reported today 
the retail giant last week created a task force to help group 
employees relocate and another to help their spouses find new jobs 
leading many to speculate sears had decided to move out of the 
chicago area a source in the company told the chicago tribune 
but the paper which did not identify the source said a company 
memo circulated last week denied that the creation of the task 
forces implied a move out of illinois the merchandise group 
employs 6000 people 
sources told both the tribune and the chicago suntimes that it 
appeared a decision on where to move the group would be announced 
this week 
the tribune reported that sears had decided against moving the 
group to suburban hoffman estates but had not ruled out a site 
near ohare international airport several cities in north 
carolina texas and other states are reportedly in the running 
sears officials have steadfastedly declined to comment publicly 
on the rumors and reports of the companys intentions and 
spokesman gordon jones remained tightlipped today 
im not commenting on any of the reports he said all we 
have said is that we would hope to make the announcement sometime 
this month 
sears the nations largest retailer in october announced plans 
to sell its landmark sears tower the worlds tallest office 
building and move the merchandise group out of the skyscraper 
the move was part of a company restructuring that included a new 
low pricing strategy and a paring of sears nonretail operations 
