the stock market rebounded today as concerns 
about the political situation in china abated somewhat 
the dow jones average of 30 industrial stocks was up 1434 to 
249504 as of 11 am edt after falling 37 points on monday 
advancing issues were ahead of decliners by a margin of about 7 
to 4 with 774 stocks rising 454 falling and 517 unchanged on the 
new york stock exchange 
volume on the big board came to 5888 million shares after the 
first 90 minutes of trading 
jack barbanel a first vice president with gruntal amp co inc 
said the market whose sharp decline monday was partly attributed 
to worries about china believed that over the longterm the more 
conservative side of the chinese government would fall leaving 
more democratic forces running the country 
although the market expected more fighting in china in the near 
future traders were reassured by the possibility of a more 
peaceful future there barbanel said 
barbanel also blamed mondays drop on wall street to continuing 
concern about the economy and to program selling he said that 
although stocks were doing better psychologically today there was 
still room for more pullbacks because prices remain high 
leading the nyses most active list today was rjr holdings 
which rose to 23 after rjr nabisco said it was selling five food 
businesses for 25 billion the sales were expected as part of the 
