<TEXT>
northern telecom inc will lay off 665 
employees in nashville as part of a massive reorganization 
announced last december company officials say 
the companys nashville office complex which had 850 fulltime 
and parttime employees at the beginning of this year will be 
reduced to about 185 workers by years end as its manufacturing 
segment is shut down the officials confirmed monday 
spokesman jeff benson said many hightech jobs and equipment 
will be moved to other states although the firms headquarters and 
a telephone refurbishing operation will remain in nashville 
the majority will go to santa clara calif and research 
triangle park near raleigh nc benson said 
northern telecom inc is a subsidiary of northern telecom ltd 
which announced a reorganization dec 6 to cut employment worldwide 
by 5 percent northern telecom ltd based in toronto has 50000 
employees worldwide and 22000 in the united states total revenues 
last year were 54 billion with twothirds of that coming from 
us operations 
