<TEXT>
douglas aircraft co became the latest big us 
company to pull expatriate workers from striferacked china today 
chartering a plane to withdraw its 51 people from shanghai and two 
other cities 
the move by the division of mcdonnell douglas corp a partner 
in a jointventure aircraft assembly plant outside shanghai was an 
aboutface from the companys position a day earlier when it said 
business was normal 
the company also became one of the first us businesses to 
charter a plane for evacuations and one of the first with big 
operations outside beijing to withdraw up to now most of the 
evacuees have been from the capital which has been in turmoil 
since the weekend when troops killed hundreds of civilians 
weve changed our situation in china we decided last night to 
begin pulling our people out of china back to hong kong douglas 
aircraft spokesman donald hanson said from company headquarters in 
long beach calif the situation apparently has changed 
overnight 
hanson said the companys 43 people based just outside shanghai 
seven people based in the southwest city of chengdu and one 
representative in the northeast industrial center of shenyang would 
leave as soon as possible 
many other us businesses that had reacted cautiously toward 
chinas political crisis also have been withdrawing workers from 
beijing and a growing number are becoming gloomy about the 
longerterm impact to their investments 
now with this random shooting in beijing its no longer fun 
anyone who approaches a window risks his life jerome cohen an 
international lawyer who helped pioneer the american business 
presence in china said monday 
with respect to our own staff i think it is time to withdraw 
for a while said cohen whose firm of paul weiss rifkind 
wharton amp garrison has offices in china until this weekend i 
thought that was unwarranted but now we have to think of peoples 
safety 
united airlines the only us carrier to beijing was heavily 
booked on its 400seat flight out of the capital today spokeswoman 
sara dornacker said 
by early this afternoon the airline had not added any flights 
although there were reports the us embassy in beijing was trying 
to charter planes to help evacuate american nationals 
ms dornacker said ual was continuing to deliberately delay the 
tokyobeijing leg of its regular ustobeijing flight by 15 hours 
to avoid an overnight layover in the capital fearing the airport 
might close 
