baker amp mckenzie said his chinabased staffers had left for hong 
kong because of the concern for personal safety and clients are 
dealing with the situation there the same as we are 
the implications of this are profound cox said i dont 
see how anyone doing business there couldnt set those plans in a 
state of suspension 
us business reaction to the chaos in china is particularly 
important because american investment is one of the biggest 
influences on the countrys effort to modernize 
more than 600 uschinese joint ventures have been signed since 
washington and beijing normalized relations 10 years ago with 
american investment there totaling at least 35 billion the 
united states is one of chinas biggest trading partners 
a political uncertainty and a standoff is one thing a 
massacre is another said martin weil a spokesman for the us 
china business council a washingtonbased organization of american 
companies everybodys going to have to factor that in 
general electric co international business machines corp and 
chrysler corp were among companies that said they had evacuated 
people because of the violence in beijing and the growing 
uncertainty elsewhere in the country 
