european companies have decided to form a new industrial alliance 
called european future large aircraft group or euroflag the group 
will study a new military plane to replace the aging francogerman 
transall and the c130 hercules made by lockheedgeorgia co of the 
united states he said 
in addition to aerospatiale the companies associated in euroflag 
are british aerospace plc messerschmittboelkowblohm gmbh of west 
germany casa of spain and italys aeritalia the first four 
companies are already partners in airbus industrie the european 
consortium that builds the airbus family of commercial jets 
martre told reporters the agreement effectively puts an end to a 
previous accord called future international military airlifter or 
fima in which the same five european companies were associated with 
lockheed 
the new consortium will continue to have relations with lockheed 
such as consulting on market surveys martre said but the group 
will also be talking to other us aircraft manufacturers 
the european companies and lockheed have been carrying out 
preliminary studies of a new military transport aircraft for several 
years in anticipation of natos need to find a successor to the 
hercules and the transall which is made jointly by aerospatiale and 
west germanys mbb 
but nato has so far failed to come up with any definition of the 
kind of the aircraft that it requires 
industry observers said the europeans decided to take advantage 
of the uncertainty surrounding natos intentions to break their 
formal ties with lockheed 
the decision means they will be able to link up with the us 
company that is eventually selected to produce the american version 
of the aircraft 
